 natural history, telluric philosophy, new materialism, theory and philosophy. The study will transform our understanding of baroque art and architecture, sanctity and Naples. Bristling with new archival materials and historical insights, this study lifts the baroque from its previous marginalisation to engage fiercely with materiality and potentiality and thus unleash baroque art and architecture as productive and transformational.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArchitecture and religion. 0aArchitecture and societyzItalyzNaplesxHistoryy17th century. 0aArchitecture, BaroquezItalyzNaples. 0aArt, BaroquezItalyzNaples. 0aChurch decoration and ornamentzItalyzNaples. 0aReligious architecturezItalyzNaples. 7aART / History / Baroque & Rococo.2bisacsh  aNaples.  aSan Gennaro.  aTreasury Chapel.  aVesuvius.  abaroque architecture.  agender.  amiracles.  anew materialism.  arelics.  asaints.1 aHills, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610038240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526100382423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526100382/original  a978-3-11-128282-4  Manchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packageb2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles